The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Rescue team
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Rescue team
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	The civil defence department has raised a force that will be equipped with necessary gadgets to rescue victims of calamities such as blaze and house collapse.        
	The Emergency Response Team, to be split into four units, will be operational from June 1.        
	The first unit, comprising 220 members, will be stationed in Shibpur and cover Calcutta, Howrah, Salt Lake and Rajarhat. The unit is being trained in Kalyani, civil defence minister Srikumar Mukherjee said on Tuesday.        
	Three more units will be set up. They would be based in Haldia, Asansol and Siliguri.        
	Each team will have an ambulance accompanied by doctors, paramedical staff, equipment for cutting concrete and tree trunks, speed boats and fluorescent lights.                                                                                                                                                          
